# Base Sepolia backend profile

Copy to `.env` on your testnet host.

```bash
DOME_BACKEND_HOST=0.0.0.0
DOME_BACKEND_PORT=8788

DOME_DEPLOY_FILE=.dome-local/base-sepolia-deploy.json
DOME_BASE_RPC_UPSTREAM=https://base-sepolia.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_ALCHEMY_KEY
DOME_CHAIN_ID=84532

# Dedicated relayer key (never use the Hardhat default on testnet)
DOME_RELAYER_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...

# Disable local faucet on public networks
DOME_DEV_FAUCET=false

# Postgres recommended for testnet
DOME_DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@host:5432/dome

# Protect relayer endpoint
DOME_RELAYER_SECRET=change-me

DOME_RATE_LIMIT_RPC_PER_MIN=120
DOME_RATE_LIMIT_RELAYER_PER_MIN=10
```

## Relayer funding

The relayer wallet pays gas for `POST /relayer/withdraw`. After deploy, send Base Sepolia ETH to the address derived from `DOME_RELAYER_PRIVATE_KEY` (or the deployer if you reuse that key).

Check balance:

```bash
curl -s "$DOME_BASE_RPC_UPSTREAM" \
  -H 'content-type: application/json' \
  -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"eth_getBalance","params":["0xYOUR_RELAYER","latest"]}'
```

## Health check

```bash
curl -s http://YOUR_HOST:8788/health | jq
```

Expect `ok: true`, matching `chainId: 84532`, and a non-zero `indexer.lastIndexedBlock` after deposits.

## Client configuration

Point `@dome/sdk-evm` at the hosted backend and circuits:

```bash
DOME_EVM_INDEXER_URL=https://backend.example.com
DOME_BASE_RPC=https://base-sepolia.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_ALCHEMY_KEY
DOME_ETH_POOL_ADDRESS=0x... # from base-sepolia-deploy.json
DOME_FEE_RECIPIENT_ADDRESS=0x... # from base-sepolia-deploy.json
DOME_CIRCUIT_KEY_BASE_PATH=https://cdn.example.com/dome/circuits/transaction
```

There is no `/dev/fund` on testnet — fund user wallets via a normal faucet or transfer.
